TRIACTINES. Regular (equiangular and equiradiate), but there are also subregular (sagittal) spicules. Actines are cylindrical to slightly conical with sharp tips (
Fig. 3C
). Size: 90.5/8.0 µm.

The genus
Ascandra
is so far composed of 13 species:
A. falcata Haeckel, 1872
;
A. ascandroides ( Borojević, 1971 )
;
A. atlantica (Thacker, 1908)
;
A. biscayae ( Borojević & Boury-Esnault, 1987 )
;
A. brandtae (Rapp et al. , 2013)
;
A. contorta (Bowerbank, 1866)
;
A. corallicola (Rapp, 2006)
;
A. crewsi Van Soest & De Voogd, 2015
;
A. densa Haeckel, 1872
;
A. kakaban Van Soest & De Voogd, 2015
;
A. loculosa (Dendy, 1891)
;
A. minchini Borojević, 1966
; and
A. sertularia Haeckel, 1872
.
